Integrating INF expression features and clinical survival information in LUAD, single-factor Cox analysis was conducted using the “survival” R script to determine INF prognostic variables. The LASSO function model was constructed using the “glmnet” R package to identify prognostic variables of INF features. Furthermore, multi-factor Cox analysis identified independent prognostic variables of INF, calculating risk coefficients for each variable. INF scores for each LUAD sample were evaluated based on risk coefficients and expression features using the formula: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
